Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,Ugzq96_s9mK8hAASThR4AaABAg,,@iansammy620,"It's very telling that all the countries in the list are first world, mostly European countries. The writer, I think, is indeed American - little or no regard for non-white or lesser developed countries. We in the Global South also have the same feelings about Americans - they have always been a bit rude, loud and pushy (to tick all the stereotypes!), but we have always seen them as sightly loud, too rich and wasteful, but basically good people. However, the USA's current world view and the administration's arrogance and geo-political positioning has turned most people against Americans. Yes, I know many very nice and polite Americans and I have a few friends and family who live in the USA. But when you vote in a regime that is so arrogant and vile, then unfortunately the world has no choice but to paint all Americans with same brush.",2026-04-25T11:55:29Z,2026-04-25T11:55:29Z,0,False,0.0,2026-04-26T09:53:14.277160
