Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxFxc-RkCRrFE3j_GN4AaABAg,,@barbmoser6209,"I am a dual Canadian/German Citizen living in France.  I can speak to France, Germany, Spain, the Netherlands and Canada.  France has always tolerated Americans, but have  little respect for them, they are only tourist dollars.  Germans, being well traveled, have slowly been losing respect for Americans.  Spain and the Netherlands have major problems with the British and American tourists and well Canada….we have always had a love/hate relationship with the USA.  What I hear and observe is absolute hypocrisy in demanding everyone speak English in American and every country they visit,  Americans do not take the time to learn a few key phrases that would make them more approachable, because…”everyone should speak English”.  Americans are so immersed in their own culture, they have no respect for anyone else’s.  Americans are loud…we can spot and hear an American anywhere.  Americans are demanding and think they are better than everyone else.  Americans are uneducated, especially regarding where they are traveling to, so Americans will offend people, but Americans don’t notice, nor do they care.  When Americans learn to be respectful, they will have a much better time traveling.",2026-04-25T11:18:41Z,2026-04-25T11:18:41Z,0,False,0.0,2026-04-26T09:53:14.277180
