Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AVpb6Tg8Dey,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@Tony-j2p5z,IDF snipers killed two Christian women in a church in Gaza so is it surprising that they would destroy a statue of Jesus?,2026-04-20T16:53:50Z,2026-04-20T16:53:50Z,3,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.675625
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AVpcn8rSg1V,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@natty5129,"I spent 12 consecutive winters in a northern Peruvian town, which grew in tourism.  I experienced many loud Americans but have two standout examples.  I went for a stroll with an American couple who were busy taking pictures of the sights.  They wanted to take a picture of a poor child sitting outside a shack.  I explained that the locals believed that having their pictures taken steals a bit of their soul, so suggested they ask for permission first.. to which the man replied""well I am American and they just need to get used to it"".  He then proceeded to tell me that the locals needed to be educated!  Grrr.  The other was me sitting in a Cafe next to a group of young American Peace Core volunteers, listening to them disparage and make fun of the villages and customs where they were ""helping"".  I just kept thinking about the villages having survived generations in the remoteness, and how not one of these entitled brats would survive more than a few days... Ugh.",2026-04-20T17:08:32Z,2026-04-20T17:08:32Z,18,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.675630
