Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AVplPlI_WWS,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@Salty_Bee,"I'm of two minds regarding Americans. Most of the Americans from the northern states are more like us in that they're quieter and more polite. Some of them you wouldn't recognize as American if they didn't tell you. Most of the Americans from the mid and southern states are loud, obnoxious, entitled, and think they're exceptional just for being born in the US. Of course, there's crossovers and not everyone fits the stereotypes, but this seems to be the general pattern. 

Having said that, I have lost all respect for all Americans. This ""exceptional"" population of people seem exceptionally good at doing nothing to help themselves. There's a bunch of well-known American YTers I still watch for their 'boots on the ground' info, but lately I find myself thinking 'why are you not calling for a revolution instead of just reporting the news or ranting about your country'. I love Josh, but ffs, he could use his platform to help organize Americans into a general strike. They all could - Secular Talk, MeidasTouch, IHIP, all of them. But they're not. Why the fck not? If every single American YTer used their platform to infect other Americans with righteous anger and encouraged a general strike, I think it could take off. Large Man Abroad and Jack Cocchiarella will often have angry rants and question why Americans aren't doing anything, but it's not enough. These people all need to take it upon themselves to fcking do something for their country and galvanize their American viewership into action. The MAGA movement took over because this is what the far-right does. The centre and left are too busy being the reasonable ones to get anything accomplished. It's pathetic. Until American YTers start to use their platforms to try to enact change, I don't want any American in Canada. Get your goddamn house in order, and until you do, stay the fck out of mine.

