Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AVppIYueq-c,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@1020-k8z,"I'm in Victoria BC and used to see mainly Washington state plates around town. I still see them, but in the past year I've also seen Vermont, New York, Kansas, Florida, Georgia. These people are far from home and it seems more USians are vacationing here. Yesterday I chatted with a woman working in my favorite book store. She said she was American and she and her husband were in Canada during the last US election. They voted in the Amerian election FROM Canada, saw the result and decided to stay right here in Canada. So without asking, I knew they didn't vote for Trump. I haven't met any rude USians here but I don't usually go to the heavily touristed areas in my city.",2026-04-20T18:57:49Z,2026-04-20T18:57:49Z,14,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.675753
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AVppqGo209J,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@pe8211,"@markopecinovic4475 We're obviously talking about different cohorts. Plus, as I've said often on this channel, I HAVE met salt-of-the-earth USians whom I hold in high esteem. Sadly, I'll never meet them again, unless they choose to visit Canada.",2026-04-20T19:02:34Z,2026-04-20T19:02:34Z,5,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.675757
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AVpq0Y57wwe,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@ArbitusRM,"A neighbour of mine moved to Canada in  his teens with his family but he still has family and goes to the Netherlands on a regular basis and he has said that most of the people he knows there are tired of many countries because the tourists they see from them can be loud, demanding, obnoxious, and very self centred.
For the most part he said the only problems most people he knows have with Canadian tourists is technically not Canadian they are people, usually American's, flag jacking the Canadian flag.
He said the one trip he was back there in the early 1990's just before the EU was formed in the town next to his families home town they had one group of American's caught flag jacking who actually had the gall to use the like reputation of Canadians to get free drinks getting drunk and when they were asked to leave the bar one of them tried to start a fight and the police were called.
When the police found out that they were in fact American's the group was taken and put in holding overnight and then made to remove the Canadian flags from their gear and the booted out of the Netherlands.  
During the process one American tried to argue and the officer had told him fine, then they would be charged with impersonation and using that to commit fraud.
Now I don't know if those are legit charges/offenses in the Netherlands but my friend said it ended up with everyone saying they were Canadian being asked to see their passports for the next while.",2026-04-20T19:04:06Z,2026-04-20T19:06:55Z,16,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.675762
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AVprBB5-oI6,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@norbertkuhn4072,"@trevordavies5486  I’m from Berlin, too. I’ll never forget a few years ago—a few years ago, I had relatives visiting, and we went out to eat and shop at Alexanderplatz. Then we got hungry and went to eat at Mal of Berlin. There were lots of people and tourists sitting around us. Many different languages were being spoken, which is completely normal there. Spanish, English, Dutch, Russian, French, and of course German, etc. We were sitting at a table next to a group of American citizens, and one of them said, “Why are there so many foreigners here, anyway?” Which made me smile quite a bit—we were talking in German. One of the Americans said they’d been in Berlin for three days and had already seen a lot. Suddenly he turned to us and asked what language we were speaking. That gave me a fit of laughter, and I told him in English: “First of all, you’re the foreigners here, and—oh my, oh my—in Germany, the locals speak German to each other. Haven’t you figured that out after three days?” The guy turned red as a tomato and looked completely dumbfounded. We certainly had a good laugh.",2026-04-20T19:14:18Z,2026-04-20T19:14:18Z,14,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.675770
