Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AVqQqjdgKTA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@AndreasScout,"I live in Zurich Switzerland ( originally from another EU country but moved there for work in Swiss finance sector and stayed. I had 3 nationalities because i was born prematurely in the US when my parents were visiting family but i gave my US citizenship up in 2025, just like my grandma.. she has dual citizenship ( swiss american.. so now she is just Swiss and lives with me ). For work ( i own, co own ( usually majority share) an number of companies spread over the entirety of EU) i do travel a lot and to that point i have come across a ton of americans. Most of the stereotypes apply.

1. Blusteringly boisterous and boorish. being loudmouths is not a good look for anyone but when you have that behavior its 50-50... either Americans or CCP chinese. Have to say most chinese are more nasty than americans. 
