Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AVtoiiGyFHu,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@mary-anneswanson1428,Does running into a maga hat when you walk out of a local store…… I’m so proud of my self that I didn’t tell him where he could put that hat 😠.,2026-04-22T08:09:45Z,2026-04-22T08:09:45Z,0,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.675998
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AVu0fq09kDt,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@marcor6769,"SAfrican-born/Portuguese dual national here, now living in Austria. When I lived in Portugal as a student, I worked in the tourist industry in part-time jobs. Even back then (late '80s & early '90s) we rolled our eyes at the lack of cultural awareness and self-awareness of US Americans. In Coimbra, we'd get tourist coaches arriving from Spain and often, (yup,really), there'd be US citizens thinking they were still in Spain. I quickly learnt to distinguish some Canadian accents from North American accents in general (it's easier when one is a native English speaker as I am) to avoid ""insulting"" Canadians by automatically assuming they were US citizens based on the similar North American accents.
However, the animosity shown towards USAmericans today has more to do with the Digital Nomad culture the Portuguese government actively forstered the last decade or so. There has been a huge influx of Digital Nomad residents settling in Lisboa, Madeira etc. A good many of these are US citizens. I heard 15 000 settled in Lisboa alone (I can stand to be corrected). Unfortunately, while they may be for the most part, in my experience, respectful and self-aware, they are pushing up rental and sales prices of homes wherever they settle. THAT is the primary reason behind the annoyance shown by the Portuguese.
But I guess  it could get worse when orangeMcEffFace actually notices us. We tend to be overlooked and lumped in with Spain (our pet peeve as a small country) so expect accidental insults coming our way as the Useful Idiot insults the Spanish more since their outspoken and much-admired Spanish PM is attacked for his principled stances. 
Wish we'd follow suit.

Meanwhile, in Austria, as a neutral country, not too many insults have come our way. I haven't noticed a rise in animosity towards US citizens here (and there are many settled in Vienna who I know personally) but if I pointedly asked my child's schoolmates' US American parents, perhaps I'd get a different story. All US citizens I know here are anti-trumpers; probably more to do with the progressive circles I socialise with.",2026-04-22T10:02:58Z,2026-04-22T10:02:58Z,0,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.676002
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AVu8alwDPSb,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@expatriate40,"Interestingly enough, I was in France and The Netherlands last July. Had a lovely time in both countries. Stayed between Paris and Versailles in France and had great interactions/conversations in Paris, Sant Nome, and Versailles. A week later I visited my daughter in Leiden in the Netherlands. Had great interactions with people there and in Rotterdam. Everyone I met in both countries knew I was American, but everyone was very nice to me. I’m not loud, I don’t make suggestions about how they can ‘fix their countries’, and I’m not the colour of a typical MAGA person. I’ve been living in Ireland for 30 years, so I guess my accent has softened quite a bit. Funny enough, many people ask me if I’m Canadian when they hear me speak.",2026-04-22T11:12:10Z,2026-04-22T11:12:10Z,3,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.676007
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AVuTZ9QTjcs,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@mary-anneswanson1428,@Bro@BrokeButHappyNorwegian money is no more Monopoly money than our Canadian money but apparently ours is from a monopoly set too 😊 ps my parents (and by that so am I ) both  half Norwegian. 😊,2026-04-22T14:15:19Z,2026-04-22T14:17:26Z,0,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.676012
