Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AVx19qkMGn8,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@debbiematheson7931,"@ArbitusRMI know exactly how you feel . Im from a small island in Canada , prices were decent and most of us could buy a home , now Islanders are visitors on their own Island .",2026-04-23T14:04:55Z,2026-04-23T14:04:55Z,0,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.676037
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AVzLTV5Td6C,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@markbrusberg9808,I've traveled with fellow US citizens and have at times wanted to crawl under a rock after seeing their obnoxious behavior.,2026-04-24T11:40:50Z,2026-04-24T11:40:50Z,1,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.676041
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AW-Hr1xDecU,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@NancyDickinson-x9p,"​@BrokeButHappyy  Tell him no mattresses, no internet.  That would get rid of them.",2026-04-24T20:28:29Z,2026-04-24T20:28:29Z,0,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.676048
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AW-IhEUVszO,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@NancyDickinson-x9p,​@EyeKahnography  Got an idea.  Scrap the allegiance and flag saluting nonsense every school day and teach them how to respect and recognise that other countries and their people have their own ways which are different to the USA and mostly predate the USA.  That the USA is the new kid and has LESS culture and accumulated knowledge than most other countries.,2026-04-24T20:35:53Z,2026-04-24T20:35:53Z,0,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.676053
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AW-K2DoWpML,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@NancyDickinson-x9p,"​@markbrusberg9808  ditch them and find new friends from elsewhere.   Go solo.  I did it for years and years.  Some of the travels will be solo with more local interaction.  Otherwise, you meet people along the way, some travelling same way as you, so you join forces until your routes diverge again and so it becomes a mix of locals, solo, and other travellers.  I love the varirty of company and also cherish the solo parts in remote places to replenish self amidst vast wide open landscapes.  Being ""on the road"" is absolutelly my happy and serene place.",2026-04-24T20:47:37Z,2026-04-24T20:47:37Z,0,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.676058
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AW0X7u7WBog,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@NancyDickinson-x9p,"​@debim9779  Can you explain .. just come across the phrase ""elbows up"" recently and all Canadians seem to use it.  Is it a kind of ""keep calm and carry on"" or what? Or is there some new chicken dance that is all the rave over there at the moment?",2026-04-25T08:01:14Z,2026-04-25T08:01:14Z,0,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.676063
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AW0XZiFxWMY,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@NancyDickinson-x9p,"​@expatriate40  You are an American expat now.  You have unlearned ""exceptionalism"" and learned the art of blending and not annoying the hell out of other people.  Welcome to the fold.",2026-04-25T08:05:02Z,2026-04-25T08:05:02Z,1,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.676067
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AW1yrdQ4X8a,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@rebeccaklages9783,"​@ResistTheGriftYonge St isn't a good place to park, ever! It's super busy with sections quite often under construction, also long stretches of the street have no parking signs because of the amount of traffic on it, so blocking a lane to park and eat their fast-food meal is hella inconsiderate. Pull off onto a side street where there might be parking (if you're lucky) or a nearby parking lot.  If there are restaurants then there are usually parking lots nearby.  I used to work a few blocks from Yonge Street (midway between the Yonge and Bayview subway stations) and our favourite grocery store was on Yonge so I know the parking and traffic situation.",2026-04-25T21:31:31Z,2026-04-25T21:31:31Z,0,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.676072
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AW21KVnFRJ5,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@rebeccaklages9783,"​@NancyDickinson-x9pjust the opposite.  Elbows Up is a defensive hockey term. Gordie Howe (the guy with a new bridge named after him in Windsor, Ontario) would put his elbow up when another player came at him.  Apparently, it doesn't feel too good to run into someone's elbow with your face when you're skating full speed at them (this was at a time when face shields weren't widely used).  So people learned not to do that to Gordie unless they wanted to lose a couple of teeth.  
So the term is now our motto - you come at us, prepare for us to defend ourselves and you come out on the losing end.",2026-04-25T22:01:49Z,2026-04-25T22:01:49Z,0,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.676077
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AW2Q86m9u8I,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@kimh,"@ArbitusRM I wondered if something like this ever happens. For someone who knows the accents, a good test would be to ask the ""Canadians"" to say something like "" I was sorry there are no southbound outhouses out and about in Toronto"". There is no way an American would be able to say that like a Canadian; if they know Canadian raising, they would not know to do it on the right syllables. The pronunciation of ""Toronto"" alone would give it away.",2026-04-26T01:38:35Z,2026-04-26T01:39:33Z,0,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.676082
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AW2UjCMxIaI,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@colinpatrick3350,"Canadian here.  When I was a kid (40+ years ago),  I got to travel worldwide. In cultures where haggling was expected, when given a price, I'd say ""I'm not an American"", they would generally cut the price in half, then we'd continue haggling.  Americans were generally seen not as bad, just ignorant.",2026-04-26T02:18:44Z,2026-04-26T02:18:44Z,0,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.676086
Tourism,cSHqVU3-DgA,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg.AVpR0HbDbu2AW2W2YAOWhc,UgxTYdKd_ZO1iGoT1uJ4AaABAg,@colinpatrick3350,"As a Canadian backpacking around Europe 30 some years ago, I tried explaining to an American girl that was far as I was aware, American tourists had the second worst reputation worldwide, and she started yelling at me that everyone loved Americans. I feel like she showed everyone around why I'd gotten that impression. Israeli tourists had the worst reputation by far. The story I heard was that kids were encouraged to travel after finishing their compulsory military service, and basically traveled in entitled gangs.",2026-04-26T02:30:14Z,2026-04-26T02:30:14Z,0,True,,2026-04-26T09:53:14.676091
