Tourisme,IaoMd2OhPss,Ugx9pJoCtlFe52uJmQh4AaABAg,,@murrayhill4016,"A Canadian point of view: If the Americans held a referendum, and a 2/3rds majority voted to join Canada; we should seriously consider making the US our 11th province. We could call it South Manitoba. Donald Trump could be the Premier of Canada's 11th province, South Manitoba. In the first month there will be a vote of nonconfidence, a snap election, we'll vote him out and get rid of him. The South Manitobans, in all 50 counties, will grumble about the higher taxes, but it won't be long before they find the universal healthcare is a blessing. We'll rename the Gulf of Mexico to be the Gulf of South Manitoba (only for one year to keep the South Manitobans in red counties happy, then we'll revert back to the Gulf of Mexico).

